EmptyCup - Design Studio Listing Platform
EmptyCup is a web application that showcases design studios, allowing users to browse through listings, view details, and shortlist their favorites.

Project Structure
EmptyCup/
├── client/             # React frontend
├── server/             # Python backend API
└── docker-compose.yml  # Docker configuration
Features
Browse design studio listings
View studio details (projects, experience, price level, contact information)
Shortlist favorite studios
Responsive UI design
Tech Stack
Frontend
React 19
React Router
Tailwind CSS
Vite
Backend
Python
HTTP Server
JSON data storage
DevOps
Docker
Docker Compose
Getting Started
Prerequisites
Node.js (v18 or higher)
Python (v3.10 or higher)
Docker and Docker Compose (optional)
Running with Docker
The easiest way to run the application is using Docker Compose:

# Clone the repository
git clone <repository-url>
cd EmptyCup

# Start the application
docker-compose up

This will start both the frontend and backend services:

Frontend: http://localhost:3000
Backend API: http://localhost:5001
Running Locally

Backend Setup
cd server
pip install -r requirements.txt
python api/index.py
The API will be available at http://localhost:5000

Frontend Setup
cd client
npm install
npm run dev
The frontend will be available at the URL shown in your terminal (typically http://localhost:5173)

API Endpoints
GET /api - Returns all studio listings
Application Flow
The React frontend makes API requests to the Python backend
The backend serves JSON data containing studio information
The frontend renders this data in a user-friendly interface
Users can interact with the listings (view details, shortlist, etc.)
Project Customization
Modify listings.json to add or update studio data
Edit React components in components to change the UI
Style changes can be made using Tailwind classes or by editing index.css
